Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Peel @Yukon Gold Potatoes{16%ounce}, then cut into ½-inch cubes. Place in a #medium pot{} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and enough water to cover by 1 inch. Bring to a boil and cook until fork tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Drain and return potatoes to empty pot.

Meanwhile, trim any tough ends from @Green Beans{6%ounce}. Use a #mallet{} or heavy pan to crush @Tricolor Peppercorns{1%tablespoon} in their bag until coarsely ground. Pick @Parsley{¼%ounce} leaves from stems and discard stems. Finely chop leaves. Peel and chop @Shallot{1}. Toss green beans, @Almonds{1%ounce}, a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch} on a #baking sheet{}. Roast in oven until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat @New York Strip Steak{10%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add to pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside to rest.

> Loosely cover steak with aluminum foil to keep it warm.

Reduce heat to medium-low and add a drizzle of oil to pan. Add shallots, tossing. Stir in ¼ tsp crushed peppercorns (more or less to taste), @Beef Demi-Glace{1}, and @water{½%cup}. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer until reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat. Stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} and half the @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon} until butter is melted. Season with salt and pepper.

When potatoes are done, add remaining sour cream, and ½ tsp @Truffle Zest{1}(more or less to taste) to pot. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

> Add a splash of milk to make potatoes extra creamy.

Thinly slice steak against the grain. Divide mashed potatoes, green beans, and steak between plates. Drizzle sauce over steak and potatoes. Garnish with parsley.